            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-28T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-28T11:00:00-05:00" n="727" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/9–2845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Syria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Porter</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Damascus</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-28T18:00:00+02:00">September 28, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 29—2:16 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. Rising press and public sentiment resulting from sensational treatment
                    accorded by British controlled press and radio in Near <pb facs="0762" n="750" xml:id="pg_750"/> East to alleged letter of President Truman to Mr. Attlee
                    advocating 100,000 Jewish immigrants for Palestine leads me to inquire whether
                    Department contemplates issuance of mitigating statement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Porter</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
